DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT MAY FUND THE PARTICIPATION OF THE RECIPIENT IN ACTIVITIES INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE REVIEW OF REMEDIAL INVESTIGATION AND FEASIBILITY STUDIES, PROPOSED PLANS, AND RECORDS OF DECISION AT THE TRONOX SUPERFUND SITE IN NEW MEXICO WHEN THE ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY (EPA) IS THE LEAD AGENCY FOR REMEDIAL ACTION. THIS CAN ALSO INCLUDE REVIEW OF INFORMATION, ATTENDING SITE-RELATED MEETINGS AND PARTICIPATING IN FIVE-YEAR REVIEWS.ACTIVITIES:ACTIVITIES TO BE PERFORMED INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING SUPPORT AGENCY ACTIVITIES: 
NMED'S ROLE IN THE MA COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT WILL BE TO ADMINISTER THE COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT FUNDING TO EMNRD AS A SUB-GRANTEE. NMED WILL ALSO PREPARE COST PACKAGES ASSOCIATED WITH THE PERFORMANCE OF MA ACTIVITIES.
EMNRD, AS A SUB-GRANTEE TO NMED, WILL PARTICIPATE IN FINAL SITE ASSESSMENT DECISIONS, CONSTRUCTION COMPLETION ACTIVITIES, AND EVALUATION AND SELECTION OF FINAL REMEDIES AND CLEANUP GOALS. THESE EFFORTS AT THE TRONOX MINE SITES WILL HELP TO DETERMINE IF PROPOSED PLANS ARE BOTH CONSISTENT WITH STATE REQUIREMENTS AND ARE ULTIMATELY PROTECTIVE OF HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ENVIRONMENT. THE FOLLOWING DESCRIBES ACTIVITIES THAT EMNRD MAY PARTICIPATE IN UNDER THE PROPOSED COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT:
MIDDOT; PROVIDE REVIEW AND COMMENT OF WORK PLANS AND OTHER TECHNICAL DOCUMENTS CONCERNING CLEANUP, RECLAMATION, OR OTHER SITE ACTIVITIES ASSOCIATED WITH TRONOX MINE SITES AND/OR SURFACE AND GROUNDWATER IMPACTED BY TRONOX RELATED SITES;
MIDDOT; PROVIDE EXISTING PERMIT REQUIREMENT INFORMATION TO EPA, ITS CONTRACTORS AND COOPERATORS, AND THE MINE SITE OPERATORS AND RESPONSIBLE PARTIES;
MIDDOT; SHARE PROJECT INFORMATION FROM ACTIVE PROJECT FILES WITH EPA, MINE SITE OPERATORS, CONSULTANTS, AND COOPERATORS;
MIDDOT; OVERSEE FIELD ACTIVITIES OR PERFORM SITE VISITS AS NECESSARY;
MIDDOT; COORDINATE AND COMMUNICATE WITH EPA PROJECT MANAGERS THROUGH PHONE AND CONFERENCE CALLS, MEETINGS, POTENTIAL WEBINAR SESSIONS, ETC.;
MIDDOT; REVIEW HISTORICAL DOCUMENTS AND DATA WHICH PROVIDE SUPPORT TO PROPOSED WORK;
MIDDOT; PLAN, SCHEDULE AND IMPLEMENT WORK PLANS WHICH MAY NECESSITATE ATTAINING ACCESS TO PROPERTIES, AND COMMUNICATE WITH LOCAL REPRESENTATIVES AND COMMUNITY GROUPS;
MIDDOT; COLLECT DATA AND INFORMATION NECESSARY TO SUPPORT PROPOSED ACTIONS;
MIDDOT; RESPOND TO INQUIRIES FOR INFORMATION FROM THE PUBLIC OR OTHER ENTITIES;
MIDDOT; PARTICIPATE IN MEETINGS WITH INTERESTED PARTIES (E.G., LOCAL AND TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS, AS WELL AS OTHER STATE AND FEDERAL AGENCIES, AND/OR COMMUNITY GROUPS, ETC.) TO PROVIDE INFORMATION AND COORDINATE PLANNED REMEDIATION ACTIVITIES; AND
MIDDOT; MAINTAINING SCIENTIFIC AND PROFESSIONAL CERTIFICATIONS AND ATTENDING RELEVANT TRAININGS AND CONFERENCES.
- PARTICIPATE IN COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT AND ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES, TO INCLUDE AIDING IN THE DEVELOPMENT AND REVIEW OF FACT SHEETS TO UPDATE THE PUBLIC ON PROGRESS OR IF NECESSARY, CHANGES TO THE SCHEDULE OR REMEDIAL STRATEGIES; AND
MIDDOT; ASSIST WITH THE PLANNING OF AND PARTICIPATE IN PUBLIC BRIEFING/AVAILABILITY SESSIONS AS NECESSARY TO INFORM THE PUBLIC ON THE DETAILS OF THE REMEDIATION ACTIVITIES AND PROVIDE AN OPPORTUNITY FOR THE PUBLIC TO MEET WITH PROJECT PERSONNEL AND SEEK ANSWERS TO QUESTIONS.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:ANTICIPATED OUTCOMES, EXPECTED DELIVERABLES AND INTENDED BENEFICIARIES INCLUDE: 
NMED WILL PROVIDE EPA WITH FINANCIAL STATUS REPORTS, PROJECT PROGRESS REPORTS, AND COST PACKAGES. THESE REPORTS WILL DETAIL EXPENDITURES AND DISCUSS THE SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES CONDUCTED IN THE PERFORMANCE OF MA AT THE TRONOX SITES. THE SCHEDULE FOR SUBMITTAL OF THESE REPORTS WILL BE SPECIFIED BY EPA.
THE PRIMARY ANTICIPATED PROJECT DELIVERABLES FROM EMNRD UNDER THE PROPOSED AGREEMENT ARE TECHNICAL REVIEW AND COMMENT LETTERS AND STATUS REPORTS, AS REQUESTED BY EPA, WHICH REFLECT EMNRD'S REVIEW OF PLANS, PROCEDURES, PROPOSALS, AND COMPLIANCE ACTIONS UNDER EPA GU

