-PARTICIPATING IN COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT AND ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES THAT INCLUDE
     -PROVIDING ASSISTANCE WITH THE DEVELOPMENT AND REVIEW OF FACT SHEETS AS NECESSARY TO  UPDATE  THE  PUBLIC  ON  PROGRESS  OR  IF  NECESSARY,  CHANGES  TO  THE  SCHEDULE  OR  
       REMEDIAL STRATEGIES
    -ASSIST WITH THE PLANNING OF AND PARTICIPATE IN PUBLIC BRIEFING/AVAILABILITY SESSIONS AS NECESSARY TO INFORM THE PUBLIC ON THE DETAILS OF THE REMEDIATION ACTIVITIES AND PROVIDE  AN  
      OPPORTUNITY  FOR  THE  PUBLIC  TO  MEET  WITH  PROJECT  PERSONNEL  AND  SEEK  ANSWERS TO QUESTIONS; AND 
-ATTENDING RELEVANT TRAININGS AND CONFERENCES. 

THE INTENDED BENEFICIARIES ARE NMED AND THE CITIZENS OF NEW MEXICO.

DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT PROVIDES FUNDING TO THE NEW HAMPSHIRE DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES TO CONDUCT ACTIVITIES THAT ARE NOT ASSIGNABLE TO SPECIFIC SITES, BUT WILL SUPPORT THE RECIPIENT'S RESPONSE PROGRAM UNDER THE COMPREHENSIVE ENVIRONMENTAL RESPONSE, COMPENSATION, AND LIABILITY ACT.  ACTIVITIES INCLUDE PROGRAM MANAGEMENT AND SUPERVISION; COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT AND CONTRACT ADMINISTRATION; FISCAL AND CONTRACT MANAGEMENT ACTIVITY; LEGAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING COST RECOVERY AND LITIGATION ACTIVITIES; AND ADMINISTRATIVE AND GENERAL CLERICAL/TECHNICAL SUPPORT.ACTIVITIES:#61502; OSHA ANNUAL HEALTH AND SAFETY TRAINING COMPLETED FOR SUPERFUND STAFF;
#61502; MEDICAL MONITORING; COMPLETED FOR SUPERFUND STAFF.
#61502; TRAVEL TO CONFERENCES AND TRAINING;
#61502; GRANT AGREEMENTS TRACKED AND UPDATED;
#61502; CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENTS COMPLETED AND TRACKED.
#61502; UPDATES TO GENERIC QAPP, QMP AND HEALTH AND SAFETY PLANS;
#61502; ARARS DEVELOPED AND MAINTAINED;
#61502; MAINTENANCE OF ACCOUNTING AND DATA SYSTEMS;
#61502; COST DOCUMENTATION;
#61502; QUARTERLY FINANCIAL AND PERFORMANCE REPORTS; AND
#61502; MBE/WBE REPORTS.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:#61502; THE STATE IS ABLE TO CONDUCT CERCLA IMPLEMENTATION ACTIVITIES.
#61502; THERE IS GOOD INTERAGENCY COORDINATION ON ALL PHASES OF CERCLA RESPONSE.
#61502; STATE STAFF ARE QUALIFIED AND TRAINED TO WORK WITH CERCLA RESPONSE.
#61502; SITES ARE REMEDIATED.

THE INTENDED BENEFICIARIES OF THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT ARE RESIDENTS OF THE STATE OF NEW HAMPSHIRE.

DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT FUNDS THE NEW HAMPSHIRE DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICE'S PROGRAM TO PROVIDE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IN SUPPORT OF OVERSIGHT ACTIVITIES AT MOHAWK TANNERY, WHICH IS A SITE PROPOSED FOR LISTING ON THE NATIONAL PRIORITIES LIST (NPL) OF THE NATIONAL OIL AND HAZARDOUS SUBSTANCES CONTINGENCY PLAN.ACTIVITIES:THE PROPOSED SCOPE OF OVERSIGHT CONTRACTOR'S SERVICES, AS REQUESTED IS EXPECTED TO ENTAIL: REVIEWING HISTORICAL DOCUMENTS SUCH AS THE 2018 ENGINEERING EVALUATION/COST ANALYSIS (EE/CA) AMENDMENT, THE 2013 SUMMARY OF FIELD DOCUMENTATION AND ANALYTICAL DATA, AND OTHER PERTINENT DOCUMENTS AS MAY BE IDENTIFIED BY THE NHDES/USEPA THAT ARE NECESSARY TO UNDERSTAND AND EVALUATE THE SCOPE OF THE PROPOSED TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE; REVIEWING WRITTEN REPORTS, LETTERS, DESIGN DRAWINGS, CALCULATIONS AND OTHER DOCUMENTS PREPARED BY THE PURCHASER; CORRESPONDING WITH THE NHDES/USEPA, THE PURCHASER, AND OTHERS AS NEEDED TO COMMUNICATE: (I) THE PROGRESS OF THE OVERSIGHT ACTIVITIES; (II) ISSUES RELATED TO THE SITE; AND (III) OBSERVATIONS AND DOCUMENTATION OF CONSTRUCTION ACTIVITIES TO BE COMPLETED BY THE PURCHASER IN ASSOCIATION WITH THEIR IMPLEMENTATION OF THE SITE CLEANUP; CORRESPONDING WITH THE NHDES/USEPA, THE PURCHASER, AND OTHERS AS NEEDED TO COMMUNICATE THE PROGRESS OF THE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE AND OTHER ISSUES RELATED TO THE SITE; ATTENDING MEETINGS, AS WARRANTED, BASED ON THE TSS SCOPE AND THE NEEDS OF THE NHDES/USEPA.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:THE DOCUMENTS THAT THE TECHNICAL SUPPORT SERVICES CONSULTANT WOULD BE ASKED TO REVIEW ARE ANTICIPATED TO INCLUDE, BUT MAY NOT BE LIMITED TO:
#61550; WORK PLAN;
#61550; CONSTRUCTION WORK PLAN/ WORK PLAN;
#61550; PERMITS PLAN;
#61550; FIELD SAMPLING PLAN,
#61550; QUALITY ASSURANCE PROJECT PLAN;
#61550; CONSTRUCTION QUALITY ASSURANCE/QUALITY CONTROL PLAN;
#61550; SITE WIDE MONITORING PLAN
#61550; DEWATERING AND WATER TREATMENT PLAN;
#61550; ASBESTOS DISPOSAL SITE WORK PLAN;
#61550; FIMBEL LANDFILL RECLAMATION AND RELOCATION PLAN;
#61550; POST REMEDIATION SITE CONTROLS (ACTIVITY USE RESTRICTION, GROUNDWATER RESTRICTION);
#61550; LONG-TERM CAP OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE PLAN;
#61550; LONG-TERM GROUNDWATER MONITORING PLAN
#61550; DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION SPECIFICATIONS (E.G., SECANT WALL, RETAINING WALL, CONTAINMENT STRUCTURE IN LAGOONS 1 AND 2 AREA, CAPPING, ETC.); AND
#61550; OTHER PURCHASER SUBMITTED DOCUMENTATION.
#61550; MONTHLY PROGRESS REPORTS;
#61550; DRAFT AND FINAL COMPLETION INSPECTION REPORTS; AND
#61550; DRAFT AND FINAL COMPLETION REPORTS.

